    <p>Wall decor is an affordable and inexpensive idea of design. Decor ideas stretch from DIY ideas from scraps and reusable materials, to affordable variety for wall decor online. They help create a focal point in any room in any budget. One needn’t break the bank for it.</p>
    <p>
      <b>How much of the walls of a room should be covered by wall art design?</b>
    </p>
    <p>Wall decor design should as a thumbrule should cover a maximum of 60% of the wall area. Around 40% of the wall area should be left blank. These are maximum ratios, one can experiment and reduce the areas as well. The rule is make a statement and not cover the walls.</p>
    <p>
      <b>How much wall should a wall art cover in a living room?</b>
    </p>
    <p>As a thumb rule, if you are placing a large piece of art over a sofa or in front of a sofa wall, it should not cover more than two-thirds of the size of the sofa. For other areas and corners, it should not cover more than 60% of the furniture size around it.</p>
    <p>
